&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Birgo, we are a mission-driven, vertically integrated private equity real estate firm focused on multifamily investments. We are seeking a highly technical, precision-oriented Assistant Controller to join our small and high-performing accounting team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our capital structures and entity frameworks feature numerous owners, distinct investment vehicles, complex debt instruments, and layered syndication models. Growth here is driven not by climbing a traditional corporate ladder, but by mastering the next complex transaction in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is eligible for work from home with the expectation of working at the Pittsburgh office 3 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Birgo’s Values&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;eamwork:&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;We leverage one another&#39;s strengths to achieve more together.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;H&lt;/strong&gt;umility: We admit our faults and strive to continuously improve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;R&lt;/strong&gt;hinocerality: We charge hard after our highest priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I&lt;/strong&gt;ntegrity: We do the right thing, even when it is costly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;V&lt;/strong&gt;ision: We innovate and adapt to improve lives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;xcellence: We are dependable and accountable to produce quality results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Transaction Management&lt;/strong&gt;: Own the accounting lifecycle for property acquisitions, syndication deals, and dispositions, including managing intercompany transactions, loan/mortgage modules, and continuous process optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Month-End Close&lt;/strong&gt;: Execute full-cycle investment accounting close procedures, architecting cost method, equity method, and multi-tier consolidation workpapers while reviewing outsourced bank and balance sheet reconciliations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Investor Relations Support&lt;/strong&gt;: Manage investor-related capital ledgers and data flows, executing accurate Net Asset Value (NAV) calculations and investor distribution processing while serving as the primary liaison to Investor Relations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;: Support the compilation of monthly, quarterly, and annual institutional financial reports, provide ongoing technical accounting research, and manage external CPA firm assurance and tax engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Other duties as assigned to help Birgo improve lives through real estate&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ideal Profile&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5–7 years of progressive accounting experience, featuring a deliberate mix of public accounting foundational training and private sector application (PE, VC, startup, or complex corporate environment)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active CPA license&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep proficiency in Excel and an aptitude for leveraging modern accounting tech stacks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A servant leader who is accommodating and analytical, while producing highly precise and accurate work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
